<item>
            <title>[SOLR-998] ExternalFile fails with newest Lucene libs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-998</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;reopen() causes segments to be reused, and new segment-at-a-time searching in Lucene causes FileFloatSource to be reloaded per-segment (and thus get a hit on the old segments).  Per-segment loading of FileFloat Source is very inefficient in any case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
